		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/17/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 11:58:47</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=227"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=227')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=40987&amp;TOPIC_ID=5088&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Hate+management+with+FD&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         FD is your friend.  Learn to "yo-yo" on big raids.  i.e. cast and feign, cast and feign.  It will save your life.</P><P>A successfull FD will always remove you from (or at least lower your place on) the aggro list and make the mob con indifferent to you.  Whether or not the mob forgets about you is a completely different thing.  It's quite possible and actually very easy to FD and be indifferent, but have the mob come running back after you stand up because it remembers you.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Fighting a Guardian Wurm in Skyfire. I cast lots of dots and feign. I /con the mob and he's indifferent. I don't get up for several ticks for whatever reason. Then he starts to hit me and /cons scowling.</P><P>FD *IS* broken.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>No, it's not.  A successful FD (obviously) only effects hate generated up to that point.  If you FD while you have DoTs running on a mob you'll loose all the aggro generated before you feign, and any DoT damage aggro generated while you are down.  As soon as you stand up, the next DoT tick puts you right back on the aggro list.</P><P>This is easy to test.  Find a mob that is not normally KoS to you.  DoT it and FD.  While you're down, it will /con indifferent.  Now, stand up before the DoT wears off and /con it again.  If you stood up between DoT ticks, the mob will /con whatever it normally does to you.  Then, on the next DoT tick it will go aggro.</P><P>The trick to yo-yo'ing to reduce aggro is knowing when to stay down.  On big mobs, I normally stick a couple of slow starting DoTs on (like splurt and ignite blood), then land ebolt and FD...and stay down at least until ebolt runs out.  It really all depends on the mob and your tanks though...your milage may vary.</P><P>This works better for monks in combat because melee damage is not persistent like DoTs and each feign for them is much more effective at removing prior aggro.</P><P>I have been summoned in the middle of casting FD and channeled it off anyway...that was rather humorous.</P><P></P><P>--Nergal Teir'Draconis, Children of the Phoenix (Tunare)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

