        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         How FD works is a very good question.  I have heard it works kind of like the Wizards' concussion spell (a successful FD lowers your argro value so many points) and I have heard that it just marks you as an invalid target for mobs (like a corpse) or it could be a bit of both.</P><P>I know that we still recieve the messages when out DoTs finish while FD, so that means that the system is still keeping track of them (and could still be adding that damage to our agro) which would explain why sometimes I have been summoned the second I stood up after a long DoT heavy fight.</P><P>I have yet to see a mob that is not fooled by a good FD.  Now if you stand up while you have an active DoT...</P><P>Bril</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
