        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I know for a fact that there are mobs that can see thru a successful FD. No "falls to the ground", no spell hits you, not in melee range (I don't buy this argument from an earlier post) yet the mob is still ready to attack = mob that has seen through your FD.</P><P>As for "hate management" using FD. An interesting concept but I would like to know what your tanks are doing that they are incapable of holding taunt.</P><P>Hate management when solo - FD is a guaranteed way to get the mob back on your pet. But if you stand up and are in melee range (That previous post about FD in melee range is completely wrong) the mob will usually instantly switch back to you. This is becuase PC's have more inherant taunt than pet's.</P><P>A better way to control agro that doesn't cost you mana is to stand behind your pet. This forces the mob to walk thru the pet to get to you and usually returns aggro to the pet. Of course if you have laid on a mega tuant spell that won't help you either.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
