         I haven't had a mob continue to beat on my when I successfully feigned death since about 35th level.  I have had FD drop because of AoE.  I have had FD fail (fallen to the ground) up to 8 times in a row.  I have had to FD several times to get the mobs to stop running at me everytime I stand up, even when they have returned to their spawn point and there are no DoT's left on them.</P><P>At big raids I get summoned by just about every mob that can summon, but rarely take damage.  Have Harmshield ready and be prepared to FD in a pinch, but usually just walk away.  I have also noticed that i can chain cast Deflux, KS an entire raid when solo, and never get aggro.  Hate is a funny thing, and certain mobs hate certain spells more.  To me, playing the Necro is all about rythms.  I don't keep timers, but rarely let a snare wear off.  When you find your 'groove' in certain situations, you will know exactly what you are capable of.  </P><P>It takes lots of experimentation to find what works in different circumstances, but I think that is what makes the difference between Necros that are played and those that are PL'd.  Nothing says twink like a Necro with a poor Abjure skill.</P><P>Teroth Castille<BR>Defiler of Saryrn</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
