        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Nope, I'm not being rooted. Most of these mobs don't rampage, or anything like that. I can be in melee range or out. They can be slowed or not slowed. I can have done 4k in damage or just a tap if it's early in the fight. I can have dots running or have none. I'm not standing up and being hit, I'm staying down, and still being hit. There is no failure message, for either me or my group. This isn't a one time occurance that I may have missed in spam, this is a behavior that I have experienced time and time again. Hell, if rooted, they'll beat on a melee, then when root breaks they'll come over and hit me while I'm still feigned (with no falls down message).</P><P>The only reason being in melee range matters for the purposes of this is that they'll be more likely to hit me if I'm close -- and they're hitting me, of course, else I wouldn't notice it. The rock golems I mentioned, for instance are usually ST'd or rooted by me for crowd control. I feign to try to make them go for a tank when they break the root or mez, but even on a success, the mob still comes for me. I'm never within melee range for that. I'm usually about half casting range  or so to give the melee a chance to hold aggro. And no, it doesn't only happen when a mob comes off mez (which was also something I thought about -- ie: the mob holding a target while mezzed where it normally would have had to give it up), so that's out too.</P><P>As I said, go to the hole or the bats in ME, take a few friends. Try it. Try it solo. Try it grouped. Try it with a pet. Try it without. If it never happens to you, then make the best of it: You'll never have a problem surviving anything. But I and the friends I group with daily are well aware that it can, and does, happen. We just call that the mobs (or mob type -- as I said before, not all mobs in a certain zone share the capability) see through feign as soon as it happens and I stay in low aggro mode for the rest of the fighting there or against those mobs.</P><P>Some necros have experienced this, some haven't. It could be that it doesn't happen when solo as often, it could be that it is a bug. It could be completely intentional. It could be many things -- lord knows feign has had problems before (ask any monk, they'll tell you about entire months when things would just see through feign for no reason -- check the patch archives on castersrealm for the resolutions to same). It may be that it is a bug in the hate list or target selection code that allows you to remain a target for the mob when you shouldn't normally be.</P><P>It would be interesting to have a poll to see what percentage of necromancers (or SKs, or even monks) have experienced this. I think I'll go peruse the monk boards.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

      <tr>
        <td bgcolor="black" valign="top">

