        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<a name="41493"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/18/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 17:17:47</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=5349"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=5349')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=41493&amp;TOPIC_ID=5088&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Hate+management+with+FD&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         But one of the pages commenting on FD on monkly-business.</P><P><a href="http://monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=164" target="_blank">http://monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=164</a></P><P>To quote a few relevant portions:</P><P>Q: Are there any known bugs in Feign Death?</P><P>A: There are a few known bugs, all of which are notorious for being hard to repeat and hard to fix. Sometimes, when using the first person view, attempting to immediately stand up after feigning will cause you to be unable to move. Sitting, then standing again will clear this, but be very careful because even green mobs will aggro on you if you sit. When pulling higher-level creatures I would recommend using a third-person view anyway, so practice using both the view and the skills early. There is also a very annoying bug which causes FD to fail with no messages sometimes when there are multiple characters on a mob's aggro list(almost all the time during grouping/raiding). This is still being researched by Verant staff, and they seem to have reduced its occurrence (though it's not been totally fixed yet). </P><P>Also of note:</P><P>Q: What breaks a successful Feign?</P><P>A: Two things will break a sucessful feign: (1) getting hit by any spell except a dispell, beneficial or harmful, including AEs, and (2) moving. There are lots of things that could make you move while FD -- steep slopes, accidentally right-clicking on a corpse (and thereby looting it) when you're trying to con a mob, or finishing a bandage all count as movement.</P><P>And yet another (the edit):</P><P>Q: What's the FD bug, and what can I do to fix it?</P><P>A: "The FD bug" that people refer to is the one where you hit the FD key, fall over, don't get any of the various failure messages, but you still get beaten on like a madman. Some things you can do to fix it --</P><P>1. Make sure that autoattack is off when you hit FD. Make sure autoattack has been off long enough to catch up to your lag; that means waiting at least 3 seconds, if you're on a dialup or under raid lag.</P><P>2. Move around a bit before you FD (unless you habitually get the "you have moved and are no longer feigning death" message). Most people jump back.</P><P>3. Make sure that the failure wasn't caused by something more mundane, like a message you missed due to spam or lag.</P><P>Also, guides usually don't give rezzes for deaths due to "The FD Bug", since it's not a recognized one. Also, VI's said that they've tried to fix this one, and its occurrence has been greatly reduced since they've said it.</P><P>Edited by - mordrakken on 06/18/2002  17:22:17<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
